      • press

        public int press(java.lang.String s)
        Press key[s]. Unlike enter(String) resolves key names into actual keystrokes i.e. ENTER turns into actual line feed.
        Parameters:
        s - - string to be interpret into key press i.e.: ENTER TAB ESC RIGHT
        Returns:
        1 - was possible; 0 - was not possible

      • pressPlus

        public int pressPlus(java.lang.String modifier,
            java.lang.String s)
        Press key[s] combined with special key (modifiers) such as CTRL+C
        Parameters:
        modifier - - string to be interpret into modifier: ALT CTRL SHIFT
        s - - string to be interpret into key press i.e.: C F4
        Returns:
        1 - was possible; 0 - was not possible examples: 
         |press |CTRL|Plus|C|
 |press |ALT|Plus|F4|
 |press |SHIFT|Plus|bob|

      • typeInRegion

        public int typeInRegion(java.lang.String s)
         Type text into the current region
 
 Unlike press(String) does not resolve keys (i.e. string "ENTER" will be interpret as text not as line feed)
 Note that "was possible" does not mean "text was entered".
 type string into region
 |Type |Some Text| in Region|
 or
 |Type in Region|Some Text|
        Parameters:
        s - - string of text to be entered
        Returns:
        1 - was possible; 0 - was not possible

      • proceedOnError

        public void proceedOnError()
          
 Use to implement Error recovery routines. Will stop test execution if there was no error.
 All the actions below this method are executed only when current test already failed.
 Common usage - add to tear down page to restart an application on error.
 Failed test will remain failed but further tests may have chance to use recovered environment.
